metadata.name: ARE YOU COMING OUT TO PLAY?
metadata.description:
No one comes out to play anymore
The streets are silent, and I'm all alone
No laughter, no joy, just a stillness
I wonder where all my friends have flown

I used to run outside in the sun
With my friends, we'd laugh and play
We'd chase each other through the streets
And have fun until the end of the day

But now, the world seems to have changed
And no one wants to come out and play
Everyone's busy with their screens
And I'm left to pass the time of day

I miss the sound of children's voices
And the way we'd all run and shout
I wish that things could be like before
When the world was fun, and we had no doubt

So let's put down our screens for a while
And go outside to play and run
Let's make new friends and have some fun
And remember that childhood is meant for fun.
